/** \mainpage Standard LIN API

\section lin_api_into Introduction

The LIN API is a network software layer that hides the details of a LIN network configuration
(e.g. how signals are mapped into certain frames) for a user making an application program for an arbitrary ECU.
Instead the user will be provided an API, which is focused on the signals transported on the LIN network.

A <a href="https://gitlab.melexis.com/swcc-tools-projects/ldf_nodegen/blob/master/doc/LDF_LIN_Node_driver_generation_utility.docx">LDF-nodegen tool</a>
is used to take care of the step from network configuration to ready made LDF-file dependent LIN API.
This provides configuration flexibility.

\section lin_api_structure Structure

All LIN API can be included through \ref lin_api.h "lin_api.h".

The LIN API consist of two parts:
 -# Constant LIN API
 -# LDF-dependent LIN API (\ref lin_signals.h "lin_signals.h")

The constant LIN API is divided on three groups:
 -# LIN Common API (\ref lin_api.h "lin_api.h")
 -# LIN Slave specific API (\ref lin_api_sl.h "lin_api_sl.h")
 -# LIN Master specific API (\ref lin_api_ma.h "lin_api_ma.h")

The LDF-dependent LIN API (\ref lin_signals.h "lin_signals.h") is common for all used LIN interfaces.

\section lin_api_mlx LIN API implementation details by Melexis

\subsection lin_common_desc Common description
The implementation of the Melexis Standard LIN API is based upon the
<a href="https://gitlab.melexis.com/swcc-lib-mlx16/lib-lin/blob/f92461045455c3d418e4444f7256ce0d5519bdf0/doc/pdf_build/prebuild/mlx_lin_api.pdf">Melexis LIN Firmware API</a> commands and events. The Melexis Standard LIN API implements the Core API, Node Configuration and Identification commands as specified
